        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1769852607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Isn't this <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddCircle#doc\">docs#AddCircle</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 571181797,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1769852710
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I believe it is. Thanks.</p>",
        "id": 571182202,
        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1769853088
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But now I wonder if there's something like <code>%</code> for reals.</p>",
        "id": 571205606,
        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1769872287
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's <code>Int.fract</code> for mod 1. Very confusing naming by the way.</p>",
        "id": 571209515,
        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1769874927
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=toIcoMod#doc\">docs#toIcoMod</a> and nearby definitions.</p>",
        "id": 571215842,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1769879811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"394485\">suhr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Reals.20modulo.20period/near/571209515\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It's <code>Int.fract</code> for mod 1. Very confusing naming by the way.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What do you find confusing? The <code>Int</code> namespace or the <code>fract</code> name?</p>",
        "id": 571222206,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1769885384
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Int</code> namespace.</p>",
        "id": 571226550,
        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1769889563
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The <code>Int</code> is to match <code>Int.floor</code> which it is defined in terms of, but that's admittedly not a great reason</p>",
        "id": 571231710,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1769894579
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's \"taking off the integer\", but yeah</p>",
        "id": 571231825,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1769894669
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would anything break if we just moved this to the root namespace? It's not like we have to disambiguate, like with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.floor#doc\">docs#Nat.floor</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Int.floor#doc\">docs#Int.floor</a>.</p>",
        "id": 571241676,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1769904250
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that we can move it, if we preserve the old names as <code>protected</code> deprecated aliases for those who have <code>Int.fract</code> in their code.</p>",
        "id": 571242231,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1769904759
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OTOH, a definition in the root namespace causes a minor conflict with <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ZSpan.fract#doc\">docs#ZSpan.fract</a>.</p>",
        "id": 571242287,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1769904828
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We can be trend-setters and move it to <code>namespace Mathlib</code> <span aria-label=\"sunglasses\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f60e\" role=\"img\" title=\"sunglasses\">:sunglasses:</span></p>",
        "id": 571243169,
